The issue here was that \x1b was being interpreted in my terminal as an escape sequence. In java to write that same character you need to use a unicode escape.

I.E. instead of printing literally

```
\x1b]52;c;SGVsbG8=\x07
```

I needed to use `\u001b` and `\u0007` in the place of `\x1b` and `\x07`

```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println(&quot;\u001b]52;c;SGVsbG8=\u0007&quot;);
    }
}
```

and that will work.

