public class CustomSoapFaultExceptionResolver extends AbstractEndpointExceptionResolver {

    private SoapFaultDefinition faultDefinition;

    public CustomSoapFaultExceptionResolver() {
        faultDefinition = new SoapFaultDefinition();
        faultDefinition.setFaultCode(SoapFaultDefinition.SERVER);
        faultDefinition.setFaultStringOrReason(&quot;Internal Server Error&quot;);
    }

    @Override
    protected boolean resolveExceptionInternal(MessageContext messageContext, Object endpoint, Exception ex) {
        SoapBody soapBody = messageContext.getResponse().getSoapBody();
        SoapFault fault = faultDefinition.getSoapFault(messageContext.getMessageFactory());
        SoapFaultDetail faultDetail = fault.addFaultDetail();
        SoapFaultDetailElement detailElement = faultDetail.addFaultDetailElement(QName.valueOf(&quot;error&quot;));
        detailElement.addText(&quot;An error occurred while processing the request.&quot;);
        soapBody.addFault(fault);
        return true;
    }
}
```

Configure the custom SOAP error handler bean in your Spring configuration file (e.g., `applicationContext.xml` or `SpringBootApplicaton.java`). For example:
```java
@Configuration
public class WebServiceConfig extends WsConfigurerAdapter {

    @Bean
    public CustomSoapFaultExceptionResolver 
    customSoapFaultExceptionResolver() {
        return new CustomSoapFaultExceptionResolver();
    }

    @Override
    public void addInterceptors(List&lt;EndpointInterceptor&gt; interceptors) {
        interceptors.add(customSoapFaultExceptionResolver());
    }
}
```
With the custom error handler configured, any unhandled exceptions thrown during SOAP request processing will be caught by the `CustomSoapFaultExceptionResolver`. In the `resolveExceptionInternal` method, you can customize the SOAP fault definition and add additional details as needed
Note that the above example uses the Spring XML configuration approach. If you are using Spring Boot, you can adapt the configuration to use Java-based configuration or modify the `application.properties` file accordingly.

