This question is a little harder to answer since you haven&#39;t provided an example input but your implementation of A* algorithm appears to be fine. However, it seems you&#39;ve got a confusion about how adjacency matrices represent the graph. In adjacency matrices, the value matrix[i][j] represents the cost from node i to node j. In your current matrix, you are trying to access matrix[i][Arrays.asList(labels).indexOf(currentState)] which is effectively same as matrix[i][current.index] which is not the correct way to access the cost. Each row represents the start node and each column represents the end node. The elements of the matrix represent the cost from start node to end node. 

Also If your heuristic function overestimates, A* might not find the shortest path. Make sure your heuristic values don&#39;t violate this condition.

Below i&#39;ve attempted to fix what I think is your issue: 
```
import java.util.*;

public class AStarSearch {
  
    private static final int INFINITY = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
    
    private static class Node implements Comparable&lt;Node&gt; {
        String state;
        int g;
        int h;

        Node parent;

        public Node(String state, int g, int h, Node parent) {
            this.state = state;
            this.g = g;
            this.h = h;
            this.parent = parent;
        }

        public int getTotalCost() {
            return g + h;
        }

        @Override
        public int compareTo(Node other) {
            return Integer.compare(this.getTotalCost(), other.getTotalCost());
        }
    }

    private static List&lt;String&gt; aStarSearch(int[][] matrix, String[] labels, int[] heuristic, String startState) {
        Map&lt;String, Integer&gt; heuristicMap = new HashMap&lt;&gt;();
        for (int i = 0; i &lt; labels.length; i++) {
            heuristicMap.put(labels[i], heuristic[i]);
        }

        Map&lt;String, Integer&gt; gScores = new HashMap&lt;&gt;();
        Map&lt;String, Integer&gt; fScores = new HashMap&lt;&gt;();

        PriorityQueue&lt;Node&gt; openSet = new PriorityQueue&lt;&gt;();
        Set&lt;String&gt; closedSet = new HashSet&lt;&gt;();

        Node startNode = new Node(startState, 0, heuristicMap.get(startState), null);
        openSet.add(startNode);
        gScores.put(startState, 0);
        fScores.put(startState, startNode.getTotalCost());

        while (!openSet.isEmpty()) {
            Node current = openSet.poll();
            String currentState = current.state;

            if (heuristicMap.get(currentState) == 0) {
                // Reached a goal state, return the path
                List&lt;String&gt; path = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();
                Node node = current;
                while (node != null) {
                    path.add(0, node.state);
                    node = node.parent;
                }
                return path;
            }

            closedSet.add(currentState);

            for (int i = 0; i &lt; labels.length; i++) {
                String nextState = labels[i];
                int cost = matrix[Arrays.asList(labels).indexOf(currentState)][i];
                if (cost &gt; 0) {
                    int tentativeGScore = gScores.get(currentState) + cost;
                    int tentativeFScore = tentativeGScore + heuristicMap.get(nextState);

                    if (closedSet.contains(nextState) &amp;&amp; tentativeFScore &gt;= fScores.getOrDefault(nextState, INFINITY)) {
                        continue;
                    }

                    if (!closedSet.contains(nextState) || tentativeFScore &lt; fScores.getOrDefault(nextState, INFINITY)) {
                        Node nextNode = new Node(nextState, tentativeGScore, heuristicMap.get(nextState), current);
                        openSet.removeIf(node -&gt; node.state.equals(nextState));
                        openSet.add(nextNode);
                        gScores.put(nextState, tentativeGScore);
                        fScores.put(nextState, tentativeFScore);
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        // No path found
        return null;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String[] labels = {&quot;A&quot;, &quot;B&quot;, &quot;C&quot;, &quot;D&quot;, &quot;E&quot;, &quot;H&quot;, &quot;J&quot;, &quot;G1&quot;, &quot;G2&quot;, &quot;G3&quot;};

        int[][] matrix = {
                // Your adjacency matrix should go here
        };

        int[] heuristic = {
                // Your heuristic array should go here
        };

        String startState = &quot;A&quot;;

        List&lt;String&gt; cheapestPath = aStarSearch(matrix, labels, heuristic, startState);

        if (cheapestPath != null) {
            System.out.println(&quot;Cheapest path: &quot; + cheapestPath);
            System.out.println(&quot;Goal state: &quot; + cheapestPath.get(cheapestPath.size() - 1));
            System.out.println(&quot;Number of cycles: &quot; + (cheapestPath.size() - 1));
        } else {
            System.out.println(&quot;No path found.&quot;);
        }
    }
}

```
The cost is now retrieved as matrix[Arrays.asList(labels).indexOf(currentState)][i], which represents the cost from the current node to the next node i

